<br>
There is one wierd thing Ive noticed about stuns and higher lvl mobs.  Giants and mobs that are over lvl 55 that can not be stuned are harder to hold agro on.  Basically from my expericance if the spell has no affect on the mob it doenst agro as much.  Your stuns do give good agro but not as much as a mob that can actually be stuned.<br>
<br>
ie  Giant for the benevolance quest is a real pain to hold agro with stun when you have rogue/ranger/monk beating it.  I use flash of light in situations like that.  So it would be stun to get intial agro taunt yaulp and flash of light.<br>
<br>
Flash of light is risky but Ive used it in Kael all day when Ma'ing it and no problems just make sure you are number one on agro list when you cast he wont even look at anyone else.<br>
<br>
Thorena the Wave Caller Cazic Thule <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usenchy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Senchy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blessed Protector</span><br>  Posts: 356<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/2/02 6:02:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15130.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Catch a falling MOB and put it inyour pocket.......</span><hr size=1> I have a macro setup and mapped to the INS key, right next to the arrow keys I use to move. Typically I have my stuns memmed in slot 5 to 7 with 7 being stun, 6 being holy might and 7 either force or the new 90dd stun spell.<br>
<br>
The macro is:<br>
<br>
/cast 7<br>
/cast 6<br>
/cast 5<br>
<br>
When I pressed the macro it first tries to cast the stun spell. If that is not available then it will move on to holy might followed by force.<br>
<br>
The spells are sorted in cast speed and mana cost. I want my fastest stun spell to cast if all of them are available, followed by the slower casting, more mana costly ones. Also stun is not a damaging stun so it will not break mez on the chanter, just incase a targeted a mob that the chanter will mez on inc.<br>
<br>
Most of the time when a mob is incoming or I pull, then I will press the stun hotkey. I rehit it until the mob is slowed with appropriate delays to use the full duration of the stun effect on the mob.<br>
<br>
The biggest advantage of the hotkey is that I do not have to fumble around to move the mouse to the spell icons or press alt-7-6-5 and miss the right number.<br>
<br>
When I am fighting a mob and the mob suddently disappears I immediately hit the stun key before looking where the mob went. Typically the mob went after the cleric/chanter/shaman, a wizard overnuked or the mob is running at low health. I can figure that out after I stopped any attacks on the casters or before the mob ran too far.<br>
<br>
Stun is your friend =p <p>Senchy Solariatus <BR>
