</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukidkod1ak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>kidkod1ak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 215<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/2/02 6:22:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15130.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Catch a falling MOB and put it inyour pocket.......</span><hr size=1> About not being able to hold aggro on giants with stun because they are immune.<br>
<br>
This is simply not the case. The key is that you can't just stun once on a mob with 15 to 20 characters attacking it and expect to maintain the aggro.<br>
<br>
Example last night I was MA in Kael arena. We had four rogues and a wizard, along with some other lower level rangers/warriors in our two group raid. I held aggro all night, with no problems. The key to it was that I knew I didnt have to do any damage. The rogues and wizards more than made up for my lack of damage output.<br>
<br>
In these situations I use <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> cease</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> and <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> desist</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->. Let me outline the reasons for this spell selection.<br>
<br>
1. Low mana cost. I can cast all day without going oom.<br>
2. Low cast time. It can be very hard to get longer spells off with an unslowed giant whacking you for 100-250.<br>
3. Fast refresh time. I am able to cast the next stun within a few seconds.<br>
<br>
To be honest I did not even really need to turn on attack to MT that raid. All I had to do was stand close to the mob and taunt, cease, desist. And then click which ever spell/skill refreshed first as soon as it came up.<br>
<br>
I guess my point is to remember what your role is for a given situation. In my example I did not need to be involved in damage dealing what so ever. I needed to hold aggro so the raid could be successful. I was able to do this with tools other than my sword. Any incidental damage I did do with my sword was a bonus. <p><bold><a href = "http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=101014">Varner Rapscallion</a> 
